<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 5 and b = 4. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.4</li><li>51.3</li><li>38.7</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{4}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}+{16}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={41}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{41}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{6.4031242374328}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{6.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{5}}{{4}}\right)}}}\approx{51.34019174591}\approx{51.3}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{51.34019174591}^{\circ}\approx{38.65980825409}\approx{38.7}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>